This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as machine translation. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention-based models, which are commonly used in neural machine translation, and could suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions experiments with a Japanese translation dataset, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as Japanese is a commonly studied language in computer vision research.
